casebody.data:
Laura FREEBORN, Appellant,
v.
Neil SANDERS, Respondent. No. ED 106750 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION THREE. Filed: May 7, 2019
Motion for Rehearing and/or Transfer to Supreme Court Denied June 11, 2019
Application for Transfer Denied September 3, 2019 William Wylie Blair, 110 East Lockwood, Second Floor, St. Louis, MO 63119, for appellant. John G. Enright, 10733 Sunset Office Drive, Suite 410, St. Louis, MO 63127, for respondent. Before Sherri B. Sullivan, P.J., Lawrence E. Mooney, J., and Robin Ransom, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM

The plaintiff, Laura Freeborn, appeals the judgment entered by the Circuit Court of the City of St. Louis following a jury verdict awarding her damages of $ 5,000 in her action against the defendant, Neil Sanders, for personal injuries the plaintiff suffered following a motor-vehicle accident. Finding no error, we affirm.

An opinion would have no precedential value. The parties have been provided with a memorandum, for their information only, setting forth the reasons for this decision. We affirm the trial court's judgment. Rule 84.16(b).
